'''''Star Wars'' 17''' is the seventeenth issue in the [[Marvel Comics]] [[Star Wars (1977)|''Star Wars'']] series of comics. It contains the story "'''Crucible!'''"

==Plot summary==
While [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] is piloting the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] through space, his mind flashes back to his life back on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]. Luke, [[Biggs Darklighter/Legends|Biggs Darklighter]], [[Deacon|Deak]], and other youngsters race their [[T-16 skyhopper/Legends|T-16 skyhoppers]] through the twisting maze of [[Beggar's Canyon/Legends|Beggar's Canyon]] when a wounded scout arrives to warn them of an impending attack by the [[Tusken Raider/Legends|Sandpeople]]. While the others try to hold off the attacks, Luke and Biggs rush off to warn the other residents of the area of the danger. Biggs is wounded by a Tusken Raider, and Luke has to take him in his skyhopper through the dangerous caverns of [[Diablo Cut/Legends|Diablo Cut]] to get him to safety.

==Continuity==
Aside from the first page and last two pages of this issue, the entire story is a flashback to Luke's life before [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']].

Luke crashes his skyhopper at the end of this story. This incident is possibly the damage referred to in some of the [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]] sources explaining why Luke doesn't use the skyhopper when he and [[C-3PO/Legends|Threepio]] search for the runaway [[R2-D2/Legends|Artoo-Detoo]] in Episode IV.

During the flashback, Luke mentions his plans to buy the [[Macrobinoculars/Legends|macrobinoculars]] which he is seen using in Episode IV.

Luke refers to his [[6-2Aug2 hunting rifle/Legends|6-2Aug2 hunting rifle]] as an "energy-rifle," despite it being a [[Slugthrower/Legends|slugthrower]].

In ''A New Hope'', Luke mentions shooting [[Womp rat/Legends|womp rats]] from his T-16 during the briefing before the assault on the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star]]. He explains to [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|another pilot]] that he has experience in shooting targets that are only two meters in size. This story from the comic is a nod to that line.

